# EtherCAT Loopback Bring-up & Diagnostics

Open this notebook with a Mix project runtime rooted at this repository.

This notebook is intentionally fixed to the loopback bench used by the test
notebooks:

* `:coupler`
* `:inputs` as `KinoEtherCAT.Driver.EL1809`
* `:outputs` as `KinoEtherCAT.Driver.EL2809`
* one PDO domain `:main`

If that hardware layout changes, update this notebook directly instead of using
the setup smart cell.

## Start Session

```elixir
alias EtherCAT.Domain.Config, as: DomainConfig
alias EtherCAT.Slave.Config, as: SlaveConfig

_ = EtherCAT.stop()

:ok =
  EtherCAT.start(
    interface: "eth0",
    domains: [
      %DomainConfig{id: :main, cycle_time_us: 1_000, miss_threshold: 1_000}
    ],
    dc: nil,
    slaves: [
      %SlaveConfig{name: :coupler, target_state: :op},
      %SlaveConfig{
        name: :inputs,
        driver: KinoEtherCAT.Driver.EL1809,
        process_data: {:all, :main},
        target_state: :op
      },
      %SlaveConfig{
        name: :outputs,
        driver: KinoEtherCAT.Driver.EL2809,
        process_data: {:all, :main},
        target_state: :op
      }
    ]
  )

:ok = EtherCAT.await_running(15_000)

case EtherCAT.state() do
  :preop_ready ->
    :ok = EtherCAT.activate()
    :ok = EtherCAT.await_operational(15_000)

  :operational ->
    :ok

  other ->
    {:error, {:unexpected_state, other}}
end
```

## Diagnostics

```elixir
KinoEtherCAT.diagnostics()
```

## Snapshot

```elixir
%{
  state: EtherCAT.state(),
  last_failure: EtherCAT.last_failure(),
  slaves: EtherCAT.slaves(),
  domain: EtherCAT.domain_info(:main),
  dc_status: EtherCAT.dc_status()
}
```

## Tidy Up

```elixir
EtherCAT.stop()
```
